AIM: This study explores the problems and uncertainties of older men, with 
prostate cancer, who have undergone watchful waiting and the strategies they use 
to manage their concerns.
BACKGROUND: With life expectancy rising, the number of older men with prostate 
cancer has increased. Nearly 50% of all new prostate cancers are diagnosed in 
men over 70 years old. For many of these older men, improvements in medical care 
have increased the likelihood of living for years with prostate cancer. Thus, 
watchful waiting has been proposed as a reasonable alternative to treatment for 
